s.length()	                    //Get string length
s.charAt(int index)	            //Access a character
s.toCharArray()	                //Convert string to char array (faster manipulation)

s.substring(int begin)	        //Substring from index to end
s.substring(int begin, int end)	//Substring from begin to end-1

**Searching inside a string**
s.indexOf(char)	              //Find first occurrence
s.indexOf(String)	            //Find substring
s.indexOf(char, fromIndex)	  //Find after a given index
s.lastIndexOf(char or String)	//Find last occurrence
s.contains(CharSequence)	    //Check if substring exists
s.startsWith(String)	        //Prefix check
s.endsWith(String)	          //Suffix check

**Comparing Strings**
s.equals(Object)	          //Compare strings
s.equalsIgnoreCase(String)	//Case-insensitive match

**Modification / case conversion**
(remember: Strings are immutable â†’ new string is returned)
toLowerCase()	                //Lowercase entire string
toUpperCase()	                //Uppercase entire string
trim()	                      //Remove leading/trailing spaces
replace(char old, char new)	  //Replace characters
replace(CharSequence old, CharSequence new)	//Replace substring
replaceAll(regex, replacement)	            //Replace using regex

split(String regex)	//Split based on regex
